column5: Theres a new tackle shop just opened in the Kawarthas this afternoon if anyones interested. He's on the east side of hwy 28 about 2 miles north of Youngs Point. I stopped in today on my way home just for a quick look and he seems to have a fair bit of stock and the sign says he sells worms too, but other than that I didn't even have time to check his prices.  Appears to be a nice little place but seems to have strange hours. It looks like he's only open Friday, Saturday & Sunday from 9:00 AM till about 6 or 7  Anyways, just thought I'd pass it on as an FYI
sounds like a good place for a part-time job Lew!
Thanks Lew Do you mean in with the sunoco just past clear lake road?
The next building north of the gas station Bosh, maybe 1/4 mile.
You could work from Lew'oclock 'till 9 Lew !!
cool I'll have to stop in there next saturday on my way to work
there is also a new place in peterborough on high street. stoped by last night the owner said that most of there stock was not shipped in time for there opening its in with peterborough paint ball
Thanks Lew. It's always good to know another tackle store location     .
